Appendix G: Resource Efficiency Metric

Definition G.1 (Weighted Resource Efficiency).
\mathcal{R}_w = \frac{P(t_1) - P(t_0)}{\alpha \Delta_{\text{caps}} + \beta \Delta_{\text{syn}} + \gamma \Delta_{\text{comp}} + \epsilon},


where:

· $\Delta_{\text{caps}}$: number of capsule additions/deletions,
· $\Delta_{\text{syn}}$: number of highway creations/removals,
· $\Delta_{\text{comp}}$: cumulative computational cost (FLOPs) of structural changes,
· $\alpha, \beta, \gamma > 0$: calibrated cost weights.

Theorem G.1 (Boundedness Under Energy Constraints). Assume:

1. Performance $P(t) \in [0, P_{\max}]$ is bounded,
2. Each structural change consumes energy $e_i \geq e_{\min} > 0$,
3. Total available energy over $[t_0, t_1]$ is $E_{\text{total}}$.

Then:
\mathcal{R}_w \leq \frac{P_{\max}}{\min(\alpha, \beta, \gamma) \cdot \frac{E_{\text{total}}}{e_{\max}} + \epsilon},


where $e_{\max} = \max_i e_i$ is the maximum energy per structural change.

Proof. Let $n_{\text{struct}} = \alpha \Delta_{\text{caps}} + \beta \Delta_{\text{syn}} + \gamma \Delta_{\text{comp}}$. Each structural change consumes at least $e_{\min}$ energy, so:
n_{\text{struct}} \cdot e_{\min} \leq \sum_i e_i \leq E_{\text{total}} \quad \Rightarrow \quad n_{\text{struct}} \leq \frac{E_{\text{total}}}{e_{\min}}.

Since $\alpha, \beta, \gamma \geq \min(\alpha, \beta, \gamma)$, we have:
\alpha \Delta_{\text{caps}} + \beta \Delta_{\text{syn}} + \gamma \Delta_{\text{comp}} \geq \min(\alpha, \beta, \gamma) \cdot (\Delta_{\text{caps}} + \Delta_{\text{syn}} + \Delta_{\text{comp}}).

But $\Delta_{\text{caps}} + \Delta_{\text{syn}} + \Delta_{\text{comp}} \geq \frac{n_{\text{struct}}}{\max(\alpha, \beta, \gamma)}$, because $n_{\text{struct}}$ is a weighted sum with weights at most $\max(\alpha, \beta, \gamma)$. Thus:
\text{denominator} \geq \min(\alpha, \beta, \gamma) \cdot \frac{E_{\text{total}}}{e_{\max}} + \epsilon.

Since numerator $\leq P_{\max}$, the result follows. ∎

